Package: tenbox
Version: @VERSION@
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: Terrence <terrence@tenclass.com>
Homepage: https://tenbox.ai
Pre-Depends: adduser
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.35),
 libssl3t64 | libssl3,
 ca-certificates
Suggests: qemu-utils
Description: TenBox virtualization daemon and CLI
 TenBox is a single-host VM monitor with cloud-managed remote desktop.
 The daemon talks to KVM directly through /dev/kvm and ships its own
 virtio devices, qcow2 backend, and user-mode network stack, so it
 does NOT fork qemu-system-*. This package ships the headless daemon
 (tenboxd), the per-VM runtime (tenbox-vm-runtime) and the local CLI
 (tenbox). FFmpeg / libx264 / libopus / libyuv / libcurl are
 statically linked, so the only runtime requirements are the system
 libc (>= 2.35), OpenSSL 3, and ca-certificates. qemu-utils (for
 qemu-img) is only needed when building custom rootfs templates with
 the helper scripts in scripts/, so it is suggested rather than
 required. A single deb installs cleanly across Debian 12+/13+,
 Ubuntu 22.04+/24.04+, Raspberry Pi OS 12, and Armbian Bookworm;
 the OR-dep on libssl3t64 keeps trixie/noble (post-time_t-rename)
 happy alongside bookworm/jammy.
